		<title>14MR SPERRY A FAMOUS CRICKETER</title>
		<content> Mr.Jim Sperry who has lived in        
 Thornton all his life, played his     
 first game of cricket on the receation
 ground, opposite the school, at the   
 age of fourteen.                      
 When he was twenty four he received a 
 suprise postcard inviting him to play 
 cricket for Leicestershire 2nd 11     
 The war ended cricket until 1945.     
 Mr Sperry had a letter asking him to  
 play against the West Indies in 1945. 
 He was famous for his lively fast left
 arm bowling and his reliability.      
 He retired in 1953.                   
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
